* **Raijin Well** – In old Musashino, where lightning was frequent and greatly feared by the locals, lightning once struck Mishima Shrine. The priest sealed the lightning in a well. When the lightning implored, “Release me from the well,” the priest granted its request on the condition that it never strike the area again. It is said that lightning has not struck here since, and the well is revered as a talisman against lightning.
* **Mishima Shrine Hana‑hyō Monument** – A monument inscribed by {{ill|Ozaki Yukio|ja|尾崎行雄|lt=Ozaki Kyūdō|lt_ja=尾崎咢堂}} during his tenure as Mayor of Tokyo.
* **Survey Point** – A surveying marker established in the early Meiji era by the Geographic Division of the {{ill|Ministry of Home Affairs|ja|内務省 (日本)|lt=Ministry of Home Affairs|lt_ja=内務省}}, marked by an inscription of “Fu” on the paving stone at the north gate entrance.
* Saplings of the {{ill|Miharu Takizakura|ja|三春滝桜}} in {{ill|Miharu Town|ja|三春町}}, {{ill|Fukushima Prefecture|ja|福島県}}.

== Reconstruction Plan ==
In proceeding with the reconstruction of the aging shrine buildings, a portion of the property will be subject to a fixed‑term land lease ({{ill|Fixed-term Land Lease|ja|定期借地権}}) until {{ill|2099|ja|2099th year }},<ref name="tatekae1">{{cite web |title=Mitsui Fudosan’s Integrated Development Condominium with Shrine in Iriyatani |author= |agency=|publisher=Real Estate Distribution Research Institute|url=https://www.re-port.net/article/news/0000077259/|date=2024-11-11|accessdate=2025-2-2}}</ref> and {{ill|Mitsui Fudosan Residential|ja|三井不動産レジデンシャル}} is developing a condominium ({{ill|Condominium|ja|マンション}}). Furthermore, there is an initiative to repurpose some of the roof tiles ({{ill|Roof Tile|ja|瓦}}) and lanterns ({{ill|Lantern|ja|灯篭}}) used before reconstruction as common materials or art in the condominium.<ref name="tatekae2">{{cite web |title=Notice of Scheduled Completion of Mishima Shrine Reconstruction|author= |agency=|publisher=Mishima Shrine|url=https://www.mishimajinjya.or.jp/wp/%E4%B8%89%E5%B3%B6%E7%A5%9E%E7%A4%BE%E5%86%8D%E7%94%9F%E8%A8%88%E7%94%BB/%E4%B8%89%E5%B3%B6%E7%A5%9E%E7%A4%BE%E5%BB%BA%E6%9B%BF%E3%81%88%E5%AE%8C%E6%88%90%E4%BA%88%E5%AE%9A%E3%81%AE%E3%81%94%E6%A1%88%E5%86%85/|date=|accessdate=2025-2-2}}</ref> Overall completion is scheduled around August in the 8th year of Reiwa ({{ill|2026|ja|2026年}}).

