* **Mishima Shrine Hana‑hyō Monument** – A monument inscribed by {{ill|Ozaki Yukio|ja|尾崎行雄|lt=Ozaki Kyūdō|lt_ja=尾崎咢堂|qq=draft}} during his tenure as Mayor of Tokyo.
* **Survey Point** – A surveying marker established in the early Meiji era by the Geographic Division of the {{ill|Ministry of Home Affairs|ja|内務省 (日本)|lt=Ministry of Home Affairs|lt_ja=内務省|qq=draft}}, marked by an inscription of “Fu” on the paving stone at the north gate entrance.
* Saplings of the {{ill|Miharu Takizakura|ja|三春滝桜|qq=draft}} in {{ill|Miharu Town|ja|三春町|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Fukushima Prefecture|ja|福島県|qq=draft}}.

== Reconstruction Plan ==
In proceeding with the reconstruction of the aging shrine buildings, a portion of the property will be subject to a fixed‑term land lease ({{ill|Fixed-term Land Lease|ja|定期借地権|qq=draft}}) until {{ill|2099|ja|2099th year|qq=draft}},<ref name="tatekae1">{{cite web |title=Mitsui Fudosan’s Integrated Development Condominium with Shrine in Iriyatani |author= |agency=|publisher=Real Estate Distribution Research Institute|url=https://www.re-port.net/article/news/0000077259/|date=2024-11-11|accessdate=2025-2-2}}</ref> and {{ill|Mitsui Fudosan Residential|ja|三井不動産レジデンシャル|qq=draft}} is developing a condominium ({{ill|Condominium|ja|マンション|qq=draft}}). Furthermore, there is an initiative to repurpose some of the roof tiles ({{ill|Roof Tile|ja|瓦|qq=draft}}) and lanterns ({{ill|Lantern|ja|灯篭|qq=draft}}) used before reconstruction as common materials or art in the condominium.<ref name="tatekae2">{{cite web |title=Notice of Scheduled Completion of Mishima Shrine Reconstruction|author= |agency=|publisher=Mishima Shrine|url=https://www.mishimajinjya.or.jp/wp/%E4%B8%89%E5%B3%B6%E7%A5%9E%E7%A4%BE%E5%86%8D%E7%94%9F%E8%A8%88%E7%94%BB/%E4%B8%89%E5%B3%B6%E7%A5%9E%E7%A4%BE%E5%BB%BA%E6%9B%BF%E3%81%88%E5%AE%8C%E6%88%90%E4%BA%88%E5%AE%9A%E3%81%AE%E3%81%94%E6%A1%88%E5%86%85/|date=|accessdate=2025-2-2}}</ref> Overall completion is scheduled around August in the 8th year of Reiwa ({{ill|2026|ja|2026th year|qq=draft}}).

